What you need to know:  Administrative checks in the WRC Safari Rally will begin on June 19 in Naivasha and the official reconnaissance of the route of the event will start on June 20The team led by Ian Campbell and Joao Passos was escorted to the Safari Rally Stages in Naivasha to look at the preparations made by the Kenyan TeamThe older version of the Safari Rally was notorious for being the most difficult rally in the World championship